  "description": "The daily VIIRS Thermal Anomalies/Fire (VNP14A1) Version 1 data product provides information about active fires and other thermal anomalies. The data product is a global, 1 kilometer gridded composite of fire pixels detected from VIIRS 750 meter bands over a daily (24-hour) period. The data products are designed after the Moderate Resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (MODIS) Thermal Anomalies/Fire product suite. Four Science Dataset layers are provided: confidence of fire, maximum fire radiative power (FRP), quality assessment (QA), and position of fire within scan.",
